06/10/2003
KIEV, Ukraine -- President Leonid Kuchma and his Macedonian counterpart, Boris Trajkovski, met on Friday (3 October) and praised the level of bilateral military co-operation, especially with regard to the international peacekeeping force in Iraq. At their meeting in Kiev, the presidents agreed to intensify joint efforts to fight international terrorism.
In other news, Trajkovski and Finance Minister Petar Gosev leave for Japan on Tuesday. Tokyo has agreed to extend a loan for construction of a hydro-electric system in Macedonia. (MIA, Makfax - 05/10/03; MIA, UNIAN - 03/10/03)
